Kiwa</b></i> is a genus of marine decapods living at deep-sea hydrothermal vents and cold seeps. The animals are commonly referred to as <b>yeti lobsters</b> or <b>yeti crabs</b>, after the legendary yeti, because of their \"hairy\" and bristly appearance. The genus is placed in its own family, <b>Kiwaidae</b>, in the superfamily Chirostyloidea.</p>"}